==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subduct
<hw>Sub*duct"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>subducere</ets>,
<ets>subductum</ets>; <ets>sub</ets> under + <ets>ducere</ets> to lead,
to draw. See <er>Duke</er>, and cf. <er>Subdue</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To withdraw; to take away.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To subtract by arithmetical operation; to
deduct.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If, out of that infinite multitude of antecedent generations, we
should <qex>subduce</qex> ten.</q> <rj><qau>Sir M. Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subduction</ent>⟦br⟧
